<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1359,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1439,1465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the from past participle 
<emphasis box="[1026,1233,1440,1465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1136,1440,1465]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Draconarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expansus">expansus</taxonomicName>
, -a, -um
</emphasis>
of the Latin verb 
<emphasis box="[151,272,1480,1505]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">expandere</emphasis>
, means “expanded” and refers to the expanded conductor, median apophysis and the distal end of embolus; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1359,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,1559,1585]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be easily distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1163,1560,1585]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Draconarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1013,1163,1560,1585]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Draconarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the extraordinarily expanded median apophysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1359,2025]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1639,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[358,467,1639,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Prosoma 3.0 long, 
<number box="[770,807,1639,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="2.1">2.1</number>
wide; opisthosoma absent. Eye measurements: AME 
<number box="[151,206,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.08">0.08</number>
; ALE 
<number box="[281,336,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.15">0.15</number>
; PME 
<number box="[414,469,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.15">0.15</number>
; PLE 
<number box="[540,595,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.15">0.15</number>
; AME–AME 
<number box="[758,813,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.04">0.04</number>
; AME–ALE 
<number box="[968,1023,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.05">0.05</number>
; PME–PME 
<number box="[1177,1232,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.1">0.10</number>
; PME–PLE 
<number box="[1377,1432,1679,1705]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.1">0.10</number>
; clypeus 
<number box="[249,304,1719,1745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="0.1">0.10</number>
